pageContext.claim: “'Look, the House is supposed to do all of this work on witnesses and documents BEFORE they send the articles over to the Senate, not to call in new witnesses, go through new documents - that work is supposed to be done in the House.' @KatiePavlich @foxandfriends”
pageContext.analysis: It is not unprecedented to have witnesses called during a Senate impeachment trial. The Senate heard witnesses during President Clinton’s impeachment trial.
